news.title: Dutch house prices fell 5.8% in third quarter, industry group says
news.para: The Union of Estate Agents (NVM) attributed the decline to rising mortgage rates. Average Dutch interest rates on a 20-year mortgage without state-backed guarantees have risen to 4.3% from about 1.4% late last year.

news.title: Nashik: About 40% streetlights in Ambad industrial area defunct
news.para: The Ambad industrial estate — which is located within the jurisdiction of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) and houses over 2,000 small, medium and large industrial units — has over 1,500 streetlights.

news.title: Mangaluru: Builder booked for not handing over flats
news.para: Abdul Rahim, a resident of Mupperia village in Sullia, filed a private complaint with the second additional senior civil judge and CJM court, alleging that the builder had not handed over the apartment, even after paying Rs 33 lakh in various phases.

news.title: WeWork India leases 3.62 lakh sq ft office space in two buildings in Bengaluru
news.para: The workspace at Kalyani Roshni Tech Hub spans over 310,000 sq ft. It houses over 5,000 desks spread over eight floors. Embassy One is spread across over 52,000 sq ft with a capacity of over 600 desks across two floors.

news.title: Goa: Rights panel directs cooperative societies body to act on leaky flat
news.para: The commission found that the grievance was being raised with the assistant registrar of cooperative societies since 2018.

news.title: Can Fin Homes mulls raising up to Rs 4,000 crore debt capital
news.para: ​The board of directors of the company is scheduled to meet on October 17, 2022 to approve financial results for the company's second quarter and first half ended September 2022-23.

news.title: NCLT allows RP to resume V Hotels insolvency process
news.para: The Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT) has also permitted the resolution professional to recalculate the fair value and liquidation value of the company as of August 1, 2022, and use that value for all purposes of the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC).

news.title: SIT formed to probe RERA scam involving 65 developers in Kalyan-Dombivli
news.para: It is learnt that Thane police commissioner was unhappy over investigation by Manpada as well as Ramnagar police who did not even begin probe in the case after first FIR was registered last week against 27 developers.

news.title: Flex spaces to account for 20% market share of total office leasing by 2022-end: Report
news.para: Co-working operators have leased over 75,000 seats in H1 2022, compared to 60,000 seats in 2021. Almost 75% of the demand for co-working desks in H1 2022 can be attributed to the three largest flex markets - 45% in Bengaluru, 20% in Pune, and 10% in Hyderabad.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh to acquire 2,800 bighas for international airport
news.para: ​​The state government will acquire over 2,868 bighas of land across Mohal-Jarlu, Chhatru, Kummi, DPF Dyoda, Syanh, Tawan and Dhaban in Balh tehsil for the project.

news.title: Macrotech Developers pre-sales bookings up 57% to Rs 3,148 crore in Q2
news.para: Lodha's net debt reduced to Rs 8,796 crore in the second quarter of the current financial year. Company's collections in India were Rs 2,375 crore, up 24% year-on-year in Q2 FY23.

news.title: Indore: 'Record of Rights' of 21,000 villagers ready, one lakh to be benefited
news.para: ADM Abhay Bedekar said Svamitva scheme aims to provide RoR to the household owners possessing houses in inhabited areas (abadi) in villages with issuance of legal ownership rights (property cards/title deeds).

news.title: Nashik civic chief wants fresh survey of properties to bring them under tax net
news.para: Pulkundwar told TOI that the new properties, where people are staying but not paying property tax, are to be brought under the tax net. This is part of measures to increase the NMC’s revenue.

news.title: Rajasthan: RERA relief for builders who got project completion certificate
news.para: The developers falling under the category can approach the Raj-RERA to seek exemption and the authority will issue exemption certificates after charging a standard fee.

news.title: Anarock aims 37% revenue growth in FY23 to Rs 550 crore
news.para: "We have set a revenue target of Rs 500-550 crore this fiscal year and we are on track. Our team is working hard to achieve it," Puri told PTI when asked about the turnover guidance for the 2022-23 financial year.
